children.value: Residences do not need to be located close to factories. Workforce is available wherever your factories are on an island.

children.value: Use the upgrade tool to upgrade multiple buildings at the same time. Drag to cover your selection or hold Shift to select adjacent buildings.

children.name: Text

children.name: Text

children.name: Text

children.name: Text

children.name: Text
children.value: Fulfilling some of your residents' needs will greatly increase your income. Others will increase their happiness.

children.name: Text

children.name: Text
children.value: Check the captain's recommendations before launching an expedition. Prepare your ship as best as you can to face every possible threat.

children.name: Text
children.value: You can change the working conditions of your workforce on your farms or factories to increase their productivity, or decrease it to make their lives a bit easier.

children.name: Text

children.name: Text
children.value: Be careful not to upgrade every residence, you will still need the previous level of workforce for your production buildings! Use the downgrade button on the residence menu to correct any mistakes.

children.name: Text
children.value: Did you know? Investor residences add influence!

children.name: Text
children.value: You always get back your invested influence even on expert difficulty level.

children.name: Text
children.value: Check captain's recommendations before starting an expedition. Try to prepare your ship with the corresponding supplies, equipment and personnel.

children.name: Text
children.value: Change the working conditions at your farms or factories to get more productivity out of your workforce.

children.name: Text
children.value: Build a public mooring to attract visitors to your island.

children.name: Text
children.value: Did you know? When you hold shift and click the pause/play button of a factory it will pause or start all factories of that type.

children.name: Text
children.value: If you do not keep your people warm in the Arctic they will be more likely to suffer illnesses. Heaters have a limited heat radius, and require a constant supply of coal.

children.name: Text
children.value: Gas power stations are more efficient. Harness gas in the Arctic and build power stations that don't even need a railway connection!

children.name: Text
children.value: Deep Gold Mines and Prime Hunting Cabins in the Arctic produce more resources than their Old World counterparts.

children.name: Text
children.value: If you run low on coal in the Arctic, don't forget that you can bring in extra coal from other regions!

children.value: The World's Fair is an exhibition space. Constructed in multiple phases, it can host sumptuous events that reward good organisation with unique items.

children.name: Name
children.value: Start with construction of next level

children.name: Text
children.value: You need a minimum population of investors to unlock the right to proceed.

children.name: Text
children.value: A collection of the most elegant and refined architectural models throughout history.

children.name: Text
children.value: A showcase of modern innovation through astonishing devices.

children.name: Text
children.value: A cabinet of curiosities bursting with antique sculptures, writings and art pieces.

children.name: Text
children.value: These splendid artifacts from the past will make our curator happy!

children.name: Text
children.value: These new devices will forward our industry to a point never reached before!

children.name: Text
children.value: These construction plans are now free for us! They will surely enrich our city!

children.name: Text
children.value: The exhibition is wonderful, but sadly there is no-one here to admire it!

children.name: Text
children.value: Have you seen those vast sculptures? No one can convince me humans built them! But they might just still fit in my garden !

children.name: Text
children.value: The World's Fair is a trove of wonder. Not of the past, but of the future! Who knows, we may even land on the Moon one day !

children.name: Text
children.value: Columns, exotic motifs and other monumental architecture! The World's Fair has become a portal to other, more beautiful worlds!

children.name: Text
children.value: There is a problem at the World's Fair. Everything is on hold until you find a solution!

children.name: Text
children.value: The event will start a bit later than expected; more investors would help speed things up.

children.name: Text
children.value: I am not sure if it was really any better back then, but these remains of past civilizations are nevertheless breathtaking. Hopefully the mummies and dinosaurs won't come to life and escape!

children.name: Text
children.value: We have entered a new era! Our technological and industrial progress is so fast, that I worry we shall not have space for all these inventions!

children.name: Text
children.value: I can already imagine the symmetry and elegance of the designs these contemporary architects shall bring, oh it shall be a delight for all those persons with vision.

children.name: Text
children.value: Finalise this construction phase before you can begin the next.

children.name: Text
children.value: The construction is slowed by a lack of workforce. Allocate more workers to speed it up.

children.name: Text
children.value: The construction is interrupted by a lack of materials.

children.value: The event preparation is currently paused.

children.name: Text
children.value: A bit of signage to cheaply embellish your city.

children.name: Text
children.value: A few signs and paving variations.

children.name: Text
children.value: All you need to design a small plaza in your city.

children.name: Text
children.value: A very elegant pack of mosaics and colonnades for a beautiful esplanade.

children.name: Text
children.value: The latest creation to bring clean water to your city with a flourish.

children.name: Text
children.value: Columns and channels to match the ancient style.

children.name: Text
children.value: A couple of unique buildings for the gates of your city.

children.name: Text
children.value: A few aesthetic additions for the water features of your city.

children.name: Text
children.value: Buildings and pavillions to build a beautiful annexe for your World's Fair.

children.name: Text
children.value: Mostly mechanical tools of little value.

children.name: Text
children.value: First hand equipment to reinforce your buildings and production.

children.name: Text
children.value: Low quality seeds that still ensure your crops to grow where you desire.

children.name: Text
children.value: Some advanced technology at the service of your production.

children.name: Text
children.value: The product of the latest research in chemistry.

children.name: Text
children.value: The best tools and structures to reinforce your production.

children.name: Text
children.value: A selection of newly designed machines that use electricity to achieve miracles.

children.name: Text
children.value: All you need for a very efficient and modern farming industry.

children.name: Text
children.value: The latest inventions of the most talented engineers of the era.

children.name: Text
children.value: A few old possessions and statues of little value.

children.name: Text
children.value: The spartan possessions of an ancient warrior.

children.name: Text
children.value: The remains of a modest tomb.

children.name: Text
children.value: Old writings, some of which are now of great value.

children.name: Text
children.value: Some remains that once belonged to a wealthy person.

children.name: Text
children.value: Funerary textiles buried with a noble in her tomb.

children.name: Text
children.value: A pack of bones from creatures long gone.

children.name: Text
children.value: Legendary artifacts that no one thought could be real.

children.name: Text
children.value: The remains of the greatest constructions from the past.

children.name: Text
children.value: I should have given away my tickets!

children.name: Text
children.value: The organiser should be brought before the Court!

children.name: Text
children.value: The worst exhibition I have ever visited!

children.name: Text
children.value: This sort of dupe should be forbidden!

children.name: Text
children.value: It left my children in tears!

children.name: Text
children.value: I can't believe this sort of rubbish exists.

children.name: Text
children.value: I can't believe all the problems that were overlooked!

children.name: Text
children.value: Please, for everyone's sake, stop trying to organise events!

children.name: Text
children.value: Definitely not state of the art!

children.name: Text
children.value: I'll check carefully next time before I bother coming.

children.name: Text
children.value: I had more fun watching reading the invitation brochure.

children.name: Text
children.value: I have rarely been so bored.

children.name: Text
children.value: I won't recommend it to my friends.

children.name: Text
children.value: Still a good experience, but incomplete.

children.name: Text
children.value: Not quite as much fun as I had expected.

children.name: Text
children.value: The event had some good moments.

children.name: Text
children.value: The whole thing still feels slightly naive.

children.name: Text
children.value: Hopefully next time, there'll be a bit more inspiration.

children.name: Text
children.value: If I hadn't met my friends there, I might have left earlier.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm saddened it has already ended!

children.name: Text
children.value: Almost perfect! The food, the drink, everything!

children.name: Text
children.value: I look forward to the next one!

children.name: Text
children.value: All my acquaintances enjoyed it, too!

children.name: Text
children.value: A very good occasion for the whole family!

children.name: Text
children.value: I liked it greatly. And I'll come back!

children.name: Text
children.value: The best event I ever visited!

children.name: Text
children.value: Everyone praised it on the return trip!

children.name: Text
children.value: Now, the state of the art is established!

children.name: Text
children.value: I desperately want to come back!

children.name: Text
children.value: This will go down in history, for sure!

children.name: Text
children.value: The best trip of my life, certainly.

children.name: Text
children.value: I never saw so many happy faces!

children.name: Text
children.value: Wandering through the exhibits was like a waking dream!

children.name: Text
children.value: My water closet has better design than that!

children.name: Text
children.value: Even the exhibition map wasn't drawn correctly!

children.name: Text
children.value: There were gross underestimations of quantity in the organisation!

children.name: Text
children.value: The very foundation of our civilisation is affronted here!

children.name: Text
children.value: You don't build an event like you build a house of cards.

children.name: Text
children.value: An architectural event that can't stand firm, that is the height of hypocrisy!

children.name: Text
children.value: Architecture has nothing to do with magic, neither does this exhibition!

children.name: Text
children.value: I could gather some ideas for refurbishing the drawing room at least.

children.name: Text
children.value: The gardens were somehow... the best designs.

children.name: Text
children.value: Some exposed mosaic in my bathroom might work. I enjoyed that aesthetic.

children.name: Text
children.value: Intricate designs becoming pieces of art!

children.name: Text
children.value: An exhibition matching the quality of its exhibition space.

children.name: Text
children.value: I hope the city council will take some inspiration from this fine exhibition!

children.name: Text
children.value: A modern great wonder of the world this event!

children.name: Text
children.value: The first stone that paves the way to an extraordinary new era in architecture!

children.name: Text
children.value: According to my calculations, the verdict is precisely... one out of ten.

children.name: Text
children.value: This exhibition is enough to convert a scientist into a creationist.

children.name: Text
children.value: A complete insult to the scientific progress of our contemporaries.

children.name: Text
children.value: I learned more at school than I did here, and my school was dreadful.

children.name: Text
children.value: Organisation similar to bacterial growth; completely out of control!

children.name: Text
children.value: Perhaps they could invent replacement brains for the organisers.

children.name: Text
children.value: Our inventors deserve a bigger stage.

children.name: Text
children.value: A stable element, not great, not bad.

children.name: Text
children.value: This exhibit with a refrigeration machine was my favourite!

children.name: Text
children.value: The daguerreotype was the best way to immortalise this fabulous moment!

children.name: Text
children.value: Incredible machines in an incredible place!

children.name: Text
children.value: This could bring an end to illogical belief systems!

children.name: Text
children.value: This will show the world who leads the industrial revolution!

children.name: Text
children.value: This exhibition is pushing the boundaries of what we presume to know!

children.name: Text
children.value: Ancient peoples might be rather embarassd to see what we have become...

children.name: Text
children.value: I felt like a skeleton by the end of it...

children.name: Text
children.value: The exhibition space on its own would probably have been more interesting.

children.name: Text
children.value: The organisation is as outdated as everything on display there...

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe they found these objects in a children's sandpit.

children.name: Text
children.value: There are more antiquities in my mother's bathroom than there!

children.name: Text
children.value: The same stuff as you might find anywhere: pebbles, broken crokery!

children.name: Text
children.value: Something like those ancient mosaic tiles might look nice in our bathroom.

children.name: Text
children.value: Those mosaics might have looked quite pleasant out on our veranda.

children.name: Text
children.value: A true homage to our ancestors.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm pretty sure those mummies were delighted to meet us!

children.name: Text
children.value: It's far more interactive than the museum!

children.name: Text
children.value: I want to become an archaeologist now! One with a whip!

children.name: Text
children.value: The excellent organisation really allowed the exhibits to sing!

children.name: Text
children.value: Perhaps the remains of this exhibition will be held up one day as those belonging to a great civilisation!

children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The event lacks a bit of ambition.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: It was rather a modest event...

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Even for a small event, security should be better!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Rather a pifflingly small event, don't you think?

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I was disappointed there were no delicate fruits and sweetmeats to eat.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Not even a single caviar canap!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Middle attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I think it's just about the right size event, but nothing more.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Middle attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The event seemed no more than ordinary in its organisation.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Middle attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: There aren't quite enough nibbles to go around.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Even a modest drink selection can make for a successful, albeit modest, event!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: You might think of organising bigger scale exhibitions!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The display of fruits! It was glorious!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Very High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Bigger events have a lot to learn from this well-organised affair.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Very High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I would back them to organise something bigger, for sure!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Small Size Very High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: A very safe bet: a modest event, but optimal organisation!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: They should not organise a large event when they can't ensure any security!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Where was the banquet? There was barely any food for such a large event!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: A large venue, without scarcely a decoration! What a pity!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I have a sweet tooth and missed some dessert there! Something exotic!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Maybe they should scale down to a smaller event...

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I really missed some kind of banquet.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Middle attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I missed something, but I don't know what... Some booze? Some decoration?

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Middle attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Large events require much more organisation!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Middle attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: If only this large event were less boring, I would have stayed longer.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The little decorations did make the place more welcoming!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size High attractiveness

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The generous drink selection contributed to general feelings of mirth!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Very High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: A very sizeable banquet! I saw many jolly faces around!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Very High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Everyone agreed that the organiser should make it even bigger next time!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Medium Size Very High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: You rarely visit large events of such quality!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Investing so much money in such a grand event and failing like this, what a waste!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The organisers should be investigated for wasting all this money.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Very Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Nothing to eat and drink at an event that was supposed to be "sumptuous"! A farce!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: If only there had been games and amusement for the visitors!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I read " banquet of great extravagance" on the invitation, but there was no such thing!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The decorations were not up to the mark!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Low attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: Still some work for the next one. We want not only a banquet and booze, but games and pastimes!

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Medium attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I can see some potential, despite the long queues for the buffet.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Medium attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The decorations could have been a bit better. It was a bit lacklustre.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size Medium attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: I enjoyed the luxury alcohol, there just wasn't enough of it.

children.name: Name
children.value: Generic Fluff Big Size High attractiveness

children.name: Text
children.value: The dignitaries really enjoyed the extravagant banquet and leisure activities!

children.name: Text
children.value: The foundation of something monumental; this vast dig site marks the first step in the journey towards the World's Fair, an exhibition space to dwarf all other celebrations of human endeavour.

children.name: Text
children.value: The World's Fair is beginning to take shape; the foundations have been laid, the scaffolding erected, and now the walls are springing up. Anticipation is building!

children.name: Text
children.value: With the World's Fair superstructure almost complete, careful work has begun on the distinctive glass and steel canopy that will make this grand exhibition hall so very unique.

children.name: Text
children.value: The waiting is nearly at an end! The World's Fair needs only electricity, insulation and a few last-minute touches to its majestic roof, before the ribbon can be cut to a triumphant fanfare!

children.name: Text
children.value: In order to blow a way through to Ditchwater's iron deposits, these abandoned tunnels will first need to be secured with scaffolding, before any explosive charges can be placed.

children.name: Text
children.value: With the tunnels now secured with scaffolding, someone expert in demolitions is needed to make sure the dynamite is all correctly wired and strategically placed!

children.name: Text
children.value: An empty plot of land chosen by the Queen herself as the prime location for the Empire's flagship Court of Justice, upon the completion of which nefarious traitor Edvard Goode is to stand trial.

children.name: Text
children.value: The steel framework for the new Court of Justice is near complete, as are the foundations for the wings. Already it is beginning to look like an edifice of integrity and incorruptibility.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Queen's new courthouse is missing only a roof, and skylights through which the divine rays of justice may flood, exposing all who would dare to betray her.
